Soak tomatoes in hot water for 10 minutes, or until soft. Drain and chop. Cook pasta according to package directions. Drain. Meanwhile, warm oil in a large nonstick skillet over medium heat. Add onions and oregano. Cook 10 minutes, or until onions are tender. Add spinach, cover, and cook 5 minutes, or until spinach is wilted. Add olives, tomatoes, and pasta. Toss to mix. Sprinkle with cheese.